metadata.description:
There's just something about flying in airplanes that brings out all my emotions. I don't know if it's the space for reflection or the idea of traveling through time... I don't know why I only cry in the sky. 

Lyrics: 

I almost missed my flight
On my way to California
If I close my eyes
I’ll get there in no time
But something bout the silence
And sitting with strangers in a metal machine
Welcomes all the flashbacks
Leaving room to only think

I’d like to pass the time
i don’t know why I only cry in the sky 

I’m stirring my diet cola 
The man beside me must be dreaming butterflies

I’d like to pass the time
i don’t know why I only cry in the sky 

There’s something in the air that just wakes you up 
Everything seems small when you’re this high above
I don’t really care flying in the sky
There’s something in the air that just wakes you up 
Everything seems small when you’re this high above
I don’t really care flying in the sky

Victims of our own devices
Six seats in a row divided 
Sudden like a strike of lightning 
Faded in a distance 
(Imagination, contemplating)
The same place as before 
(Relying on faith, having patience)
We're always wanting more 
I haven't felt bored ever since I was a kid

I’d like to pass the time
i don’t know why I only cry in the sky 

Performed by TAROT
Written by TAROT
Produced by Blake Burchette & Tate Gardner 
Mixed by Nic Laz
Mastered by Gentry Studer
